<hr>
<p class="Book"><span style="text-decoration: none">Author's Note</span></p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial">The story of Louis Riel and the <i>Métis, </i>
barely touched upon in this book, is one of the most exciting in Canadian 
history. At the present time, I have a book in its development stages which will 
deal with this subject at greater length, and touch upon some other aspects of 
Western Canadian history.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial">Early travelers in Western Canada had much to 
say about the mosquitoes and these stories in this book are not exaggerated. 
David Thompson, Palliser, the Earl of Southesk, Butler, Traill, Kootenai Brown 
and many others told such stories as those repeated here.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial">— <i>Louis L'Amour</i></span></p>

